<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">

		<table width="100%">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Gnomish Mage</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:">Ashnoll</a> | 
		            2/13/2001 6:56:47 AM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">There are many ways I've heard about playing a mage, and where to play your mage, but I found mines really good...<BR>
<BR>
1-3<BR>
These are the worst levels of a mage. Untill you hit 4, YOU SUCK! That is. without a pet, your a bad wizard, that's all. You can level very fast in Steamfond tho, because your hunting area is near the druid ring, and don't be afraid to ask High level druids to buff you...<BR>
<BR>
4-7<BR>
YOUR THA MAN...that is. At level 4, Mage are THE BEST CLASS. Your so strong for your level...it's not even funny.  You just have to solo the Kobold camp near Akanon(on your left when your leaving city). They are all yellow and with an EARTH PET(really important) you can solo all...Do that untill level 7 and then try to kill some higher stuff...it's gonna be hard tho. <BR>
<BR>
8-11 <BR>
YOUR THA MAN Again!!! You whoop all white yellow and not too high red easely..Your hunting area is now near the minos caves...kill everything except mino hero and lords...DON'T group. You can solo all anyway..<BR>
<BR>
12-15<BR>
Now You have 2 choice: Oasis for Xp, Crusbone for money...Go for Crushbone! awesome money for the level...Just sell the CB Pads and belts to peeps in Gfay. Stick with earth pet<BR>
<BR>
16-19<BR>
More choice here: Lake of ill omen, Great Xp. Oasis, Great XP.Unrest, Great XP, good loot, very dangerous. I was in Unrest for those levels...One time or another, you have to learn how it works in dungeons and stuff...I learn a lot in Unrest those levels, and I even stayed there untill level 24. At 16-19 you better stay near entrance and avoid trains...Now U have the choice...Earth pet or Water...I had water during these levels.<BR>
<BR>
20-23<BR>
I was still in Unrest, withmy Round room group...We had tons of fun there, and that's where I met my today's friends. Friendship and playership are making a group to work well, and it was like that with those peeps...Great Time<BR>
<BR>
24-28<BR>
I left unrest...Went in Mistmoore, Lake of Ill omen, South Karana. Great loot in Sout Karana at gnolls. Earth pet was my choice during these levels. Start to look for quest and stuff...You might be able to did em by your own.<BR>
<BR>
29-33<BR>
Definitively icelad in Vellious. GREAT xp but the worst loot I ever seen. If you don't get any Cougar Claw earings, you make no money there. The CCE are Very rare drop from Snow cougars...Sells for 200pp tho. I was playing with Earth pet, but maybe I was wrong...<BR>
<BR>
34...<BR>
I'm killing Giants, Specs, Cyclops, anywhere...it's really cool. I'm using Earth pet, but Im really not sure if it's a good choice...I think I should go with Water pet. Never forget that if there's a necro in your group, don'T use earth pet...It will cancel the fear by rooting.<BR>
<BR>
At 34, I don't know if there's a &quot;best place&quot; for those levels, but forget the level up per day...There are many possibilities now...Most of the dungeons and maps are available for you. I think that the water pet is the pet to use after level 29, but It's my opinion...Maybe you'll have a different choice, but you need to play a mage for that. I think you should play with the pet you feel good with...<BR>
<BR>
Ashnoll, Mage on Brell Serilis<BR>
<BR>

			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
